        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_aīv" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>aīv</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ajev</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>привлекательный</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>красивый</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>изящный</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>тайный</q>
                        </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (?)</note><note type="comment"
                            xml:lang="en"> (?)</note></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>aivaj</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>по секрету</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>privately</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>наедине</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>face to face</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>... aftæ ræsūǧd, xærzkond, xærzaīv wydi wycy ḱyzg</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>столь прекрасна, стройна, изящна была та девушка</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>that girl was so beautiful, slender, graceful</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV
                            9</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>qwamæ (jæ xæʒar) mīdægæj dær ysaīvtæ kæna</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>он должен (свой дом) красиво отделать также внутри</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he must decorate (his house) beautifully also inside</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Arsen"/><biblScope>17</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>æ tawæræq æ zærdi fændon ajev næbal cæwuj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>его рассказ не течет так красиво, как ему хотелось бы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>his story does not flow as beautifully as he would like</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1956 VII
                            53</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ajjevon ʒuxæj ʒurdta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>он говорил красиво</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he spoke beautifully</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>es næmæ ajjevon literaturæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>у нас есть художественная литрратура</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>we have fiction literature</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"
                            /><biblScope>273%l2%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>aīvæj jyn zæǧ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>скажи ему наедине, по секрету</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>tell him privately, face to face</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>aīvæj-aīvæj axicæn kodtoj sæ dywwæjy dær</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>осторожно развели обоих (ссорящихся)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>both quarelling people were carefully separated</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>51</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>dæsæm bon ḱyzg aīvæj jæxī ajsta fændagmæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>на десятый день девушка тайком вышла на дорогу</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>on the tenth day, the girl secretly went out on the road</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Аргъ."
                            /><biblScope>137</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Семантика слова недостаточно ясна; значение ‘тайный’, которое
                    устанавливается на основании выражения %iaivæj%i ‘по секрету’, кажется нам
                    исходным (‘тайный’ → ‘таинственный’ → ‘чудесный’ → ‘прекрасный’). В этом случае
                    источником осетинского слова можно считать <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>ġaib</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"
                            ><w>ġāib</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (ﻗیﺐ, ﻗ ایﺐ)</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (ﻗیﺐ, ﻗ ایﺐ)</note>
                        <gloss><q>секрет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>тайна</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>невидимый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>скрытый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>тайный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>неземной</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр., <mentioned xml:lang="tr"><lang/>
                        <w>gayb</w></mentioned> id. В начале мы ожидали бы в осетинском %iq%i
                    (*%iqaiv%i); ср., однако, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_app"/> рядом с <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_qapp"/>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">The semantics of the word is not clear enough; the meaning
                    ‘secret’, that is specified on the basis of the expression %iaivæj%i ‘secretly’,
                    seems to be original (‘secret’ → ‘mystic’ → ‘miraclous’ → ‘beautiful’). In this
                    case, the source of the Ossetic word can be considered <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>ġaib</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"
                            ><w>ġāib</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (ﻗیﺐ, ﻗ ایﺐ)</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (ﻗیﺐ, ﻗ ایﺐ)</note>
                        <gloss><q>secret</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>mistery</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>unvisible</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>covert</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>secret (adj.)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ethereal</q></gloss></mentioned> etc., <mentioned xml:lang="tr"><lang/>
                        <w>gayb</w></mentioned> id. We would expect initial %iq%i in Ossetic
                    (*%iqaiv%i); cf., however, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_app"/> and <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_qapp"/>.</etym>
            </entry>
